We recently came across an article with the exciting news that the Indian government is planning on making its Internet content available in regional languages &ldquo;to remove the language barrier among Indians.&quot;
Currently websites are available in English and Hindi but that leaves out the remaining 20 regional languages that are spoken across the country.
&ldquo;We need a method through which any Indian using his or her language should be able to converse with any user in any other Indian language without the impediment of English as a link language.
